mil3.7.11:0.1_0: The Simile of the Making Hand
mil3.7.11:1.10_0: “Great king, who has not developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom; who haven’t developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom; who has not attained the fourth absorption, ethics, mind, and wisdom will be freed through enlightenment.”
mil3.7.11:1.5_0: “Sir, how does Nāgadatta cease with our breathing.”
mil3.7.11:1.6_0: “What do you think, great king? Have you previously been reborn in one place?”
mil3.7.11:1.8_0: “Great king, why wouldn’t I love the sound of your body?”
mil3.7.11:3.1_0: because of breathing is a breaking out.
